<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="103" type="remarks">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="103">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="103">
An additional, relatively large 
<taxonomicName class="Actinopterygii" family="Myctophidae" genus="Myctophum" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Myctophum" order="Myctophiformes" pageId="0" pageNumber="103" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="103">Myctophum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species of about 3.5 mm in length is observed in the Ichishi Group and will be described separately by one of us (YT). It is characterized by a regularly rounded outline and a relatively long rostrum.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
